HTTP Server

Running SERVER:
1. Run the server program as below : 
	python3 HTTP.py <port_number>

2. For testing, run the file :
	python3 testing.py <port_number>

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

For performing requests on CLient Side:

1.) GET :
open a new window on terminal and run the following command:
	telnet 127.0.0.1 <port_number>
	GET /filename

2.) HEAD
open a new window on terminal and run the following command:
	telnet 127.0.0.1 <port_number>
	HEAD /filename

3.) PUT
open a new window on terminal and run the following command:
	telnet 127.0.0.1 <port_number>
	PUT /filename
	<host-name>
	<file-type>
	<content>

4.)DELETE
open a new window on terminal and run the following:
	telnet 127.0.0.1 <port_number>
	DELETE /filename
	Username : <username>
	Password : <password>
	
5.)POST
	a)Open web browser and type "localhost:<port_number>/form.html"
	b)Then fill the first and last name.
	c)Then a file named forpost.txt will be created in the folder of the project. That file contains the data.
	d) Successfull POST request will be shown on the browser.
	
